---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="Registry Providers"
  description="Five registry drivers for distributing Docker images to your servers — from local SSH transfer to GHCR and Docker Hub."
  section="features"
>
  <p>
    Shuttle needs to get your Docker image from your build machine to the server. The registry
    provider controls how that distribution happens. Choose based on your topology: single-node
    deploys, multi-node Swarm clusters, or external CI pipelines.
  </p>

  <h2>Driver comparison</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Driver</th>
        <th>How it works</th>
        <th>Best for</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>local-transfer</code></td>
        <td><code>docker save | ssh docker load</code></td>
        <td>Single-node deploys, no registry needed</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>local-registry</code></td>
        <td>Ephemeral registry on manager + SSH tunnel from local to push</td>
        <td>Multi-node Swarm without an external registry</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>ghcr</code></td>
        <td><code>docker push</code> to ghcr.io, server pulls</td>
        <td>GitHub-hosted projects, CI with GITHUB_TOKEN</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>docker-hub</code></td>
        <td><code>docker push</code> to Docker Hub, server pulls</td>
        <td>Public images or Docker Hub subscribers</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>custom</code></td>
        <td><code>docker push</code> to any OCI-compliant registry, server pulls</td>
        <td>Self-hosted registries (Harbor, Gitea, ECR, etc.)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>local-transfer (default)</h2>
  <p>
    The simplest driver. Shuttle builds the image locally, saves it with <code>docker save</code>,
    and streams it into <code>docker load</code> over SSH. No registry account or credentials
    required.
  </p>
  <p>
    The main drawback is transfer time: a 500MB image over a typical VPS connection takes 30-60
    seconds. Once cached on the server, subsequent deploys of images with similar layers are faster
    because Docker skips already-present layers.
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">registry:
  driver: local-transfer   # default — can be omitted entirely
</code></pre>

  <h2>local-registry</h2>
  <p>
    For multi-node Swarm deployments without an external registry. Shuttle:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Starts an ephemeral <code>registry:2</code> container on the Swarm manager</li>
    <li>Creates an SSH tunnel from your local machine to the registry port</li>
    <li>Pushes the image through the tunnel to the ephemeral registry</li>
    <li>All Swarm nodes pull from the manager's registry over the internal network</li>
    <li>Tears down the ephemeral registry after deploy completes</li>
  </ol>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">registry:
  driver: local-registry
</code></pre>

  <h2>ghcr</h2>
  <p>
    Push to GitHub Container Registry. Requires a personal access token (or <code>GITHUB_TOKEN</code>
    in GitHub Actions) with <code>write:packages</code> scope.
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">registry:
  driver: ghcr
  username: your-github-username
  password_env: GHCR_TOKEN     # name of the env var holding the token
</code></pre>
  <p>
    In CI with GitHub Actions, use <code>GITHUB_TOKEN</code> directly — it has automatic
    <code>write:packages</code> permission for the current repo.
  </p>

  <h2>docker-hub</h2>
  <p>
    Push to Docker Hub. Requires a Docker Hub account and an access token (not your password).
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">registry:
  driver: docker-hub
  username: your-dockerhub-username
  password_env: DOCKERHUB_TOKEN
</code></pre>
  <p>
    Create an access token at
    <a href="https://hub.docker.com/settings/security" target="_blank">hub.docker.com/settings/security</a>.
    Store the token value in the <code>DOCKERHUB_TOKEN</code> environment variable (or whichever
    name you set in <code>password_env</code>).
  </p>

  <h2>custom</h2>
  <p>
    Any OCI-compliant registry: Harbor, Gitea Container Registry, Amazon ECR, Google Artifact
    Registry, etc.
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">registry:
  driver: custom
  url: registry.example.com           # registry hostname (no protocol)
  username: robot$my-project+deploy
  password_env: REGISTRY_TOKEN
</code></pre>
  <p>
    For AWS ECR, generate a temporary password with
    <code>aws ecr get-login-password</code> and export it as the value of <code>password_env</code>
    before running <code>shuttle deploy</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>--skip-build flag</h2>
  <p>
    When deploying from CI after a separate build step, use <code>--skip-build</code> to skip the
    local build and transfer. The server will pull the image that was already pushed to the
    registry by the build job:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle deploy --skip-build
</code></pre>
  <p>
    This is the pattern used by the generated GitHub Actions and GitLab CI workflows.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
